Demea completes the discomfiture of Micio by prevailing on him to manumit Syrus and his wife, besides advaucing them money to make a start in life on their own account. His bewildered brother appeals to him for an explanation, whereupon Demea, in his true character, points the moral of the Play and the curtain falls ¹.
